==English==
=== Pronunciation (1) ===
[[IPA]]: /hæsˈtə/
=== Etymology (1) ===
Written form of a [[w:reduction (linguistics)|reduction]] of "[[has]] [[to]]"
=== Verb phrase ===
[[Category:English verbs]]
'''hasta'''
#(''colloquial'') has to; is required to
#:''He '''hasta''' visit the doctor.''
==== See also (1) ====
* [[havta]]
=== Pronuncation (2) ===
[[IPA]]: /ɑːsˈtə/
=== Etymology (2) ===
From Spanish ''hasta'', "until," especially ''hasta luego'', "until later."
=== Interjection ===
#(''colloquial'') [[goodbye]]

